<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A6BFF97FF4CF8FDEDD7F853" box="[151,414,1896,1921]" pageId="20" pageNumber="221" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A6BFF97FF4CF8FDEDD7F853" blockId="20.[151,540,1861,1921]" box="[151,414,1896,1921]" pageId="20" pageNumber="221">
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6BFF97FF4CF8FDECAAF852" box="[151,227,1896,1921]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="221">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
a–h, 12a–d, 19c.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A6BFF96FF4CF825ED0EFE93" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="20" pageNumber="221" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A6BFF96FF4CF825ED0EFE93" blockId="20.[151,1437,1968,2029]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="20" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6BFF97FF4CF825ED43F81A" bold="true" box="[151,266,1968,1993]" pageId="20" pageNumber="221">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Crown short; two pairs of small wedge-shaped dark brown markings apically and subapically. Subgenital plate obovate; ratio of length to width 1.22–1.37. Aedeagal shaft apex with one pair of acute teeth, adpressed to shaft, directed ventrad; shaft uniformly curved posterodorsally, tubular, sclerotized; dorsal apodeme in dorsal view elongate, T-shaped, slightly shorter than shaft; aedeagal process right-angled at base, smooth, longer than aedeagal shaft. Style apophysis elongate, digitate. Connective with transverse bar straight, arms long. Pygofer lobe with large, ventroapical, sclerotized acuminate process. Tergite X rectangular; ventroapically with paired, bipinnate tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF3866697A6AFF96FF4CFAE9EE61FA1C" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" startId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" targetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A6AFF96FF4CFAE9EE61FA1C" blockId="21.[151,1436,1404,1487]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FF4CFAE9ED02FA41" bold="true" box="[151,331,1404,1426]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">FIGURE 11a–h.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A6AFF96FE8CFAE9EE24FA41" authority="Stiller, 2019" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[343,621,1404,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thigmacaenus" status="n.gen.">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FE8CFAE9EE24FA41" box="[343,621,1404,1426]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Discolopeus thigmacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FDA3FAE9EF4DFA41" bold="true" box="[632,772,1404,1426]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20057887A6AFF96FDA3FAE9EEF0FA41" box="[632,697,1404,1426]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" rank="genus">n.gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
&amp; sp.
</emphasis>
, male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A6AFF96FF1CFA69EEBDF9EB" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A6AFF96FF1CFA69EEBDF9EB" blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FF1CFA69ED0FF9C6" bold="true" box="[199,326,1532,1557]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named for the adpressed teeth or teeth touching, in contact with the shaft, verb and noun in apposition in Greek, 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FE59F98AED99F9EB" box="[386,464,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">thigma</emphasis>
, touch, and 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FD82F98AEEE5F9EB" box="[601,684,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">akaina,</emphasis>
tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A6AFF95FF1CF9D1EDABFD57" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A6AFF96FF1CF9D1EE0EF93F" blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FF1CF9D1ED4DF98E" bold="true" box="[199,260,1604,1629]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FECFF9D1EDBFF98E" bold="true" box="[276,502,1604,1629]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">female and nymph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FDDDF9D1EE00F98E" bold="true" box="[518,585,1604,1629]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Color</emphasis>
. Crown short, with two pairs of small wedge-shaped dark brown marking apically and subapically respectively, transverse faint orange line medially (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6AFF96FC35F9F2E80DF953" box="[1006,1092,1639,1664]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–d). Pronotum with two pairs of brown to dark brown spots near compound eye (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6AFF96FD00F919EF78F976" box="[731,817,1676,1701]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–d). Tegmina with many dark brown reticulate colour patterns and some recurved vein-like markings in costal cells (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6AFF96FCBDF93AEFF4F91B" box="[870,957,1711,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–d). Nymph stramineous, with two basal abdominal segments brown (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6AFF96FE01F941EE72F93F" box="[474,571,1748,1773]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A6AFF96FF1CF962EFD9F88B" blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FF1CF962ED4DF8C3" bold="true" box="[199,260,1783,1808]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FEC8F962ED8BF8C3" bold="true" box="[275,450,1783,1808]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Measurements</emphasis>
. Overall length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A6AFF96FDA7F962EF6DF8DC" box="[636,804,1783,1808]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.525" metricValueMax="4.65" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="4.525" valueMax="4.65" valueMin="4.4">4.40–4.65 mm</quantity>
; crown length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A6AFF96FC16F96DE83CF8DC" box="[973,1141,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="0.39" valueMax="0.41" valueMin="0.37">0.37–0.41 mm</quantity>
; crown length next to eye 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A6AFF96FF4CF889ED0BF8E7" box="[151,322,1820,1845]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.5999999999999996" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="0.375" valueMax="0.39" valueMin="0.36">0.36–0.39 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A6AFF96FDC4F889EE82F8E7" box="[543,715,1820,1845]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="0.535" valueMax="0.55" valueMin="0.52">0.52–0.55 mm</quantity>
; head width 1.4 4– 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A6AFF96FC72F889E85CF8E7" box="[937,1045,1820,1845]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.50 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A6AFF96FB37F889E9D1F8E7" box="[1260,1432,1820,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.33" metricValueMax="1.39" metricValueMin="1.27" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="1.33" valueMax="1.39" valueMin="1.27">1.27–1.39 mm</quantity>
; ocellus diameter 35.2–44.6 µm; interocellar distance 57.2–71.6 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A6AFF95FF1CF8F1EFF9FE5B" blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1437,151,1365]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FF1CF8F1ED4DF8AE" bold="true" box="[199,260,1892,1917]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A6AFF96FEC8F8F1EDC8F8AE" bold="true" box="[275,385,1892,1917]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Tergite X elongate, rectangular in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6AFF96FC77F8F1E845F8AF" box="[940,1036,1892,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 11a</figureCitation>
), expanded ventrad in lateral view, distal ventral margin with elongated, acutely triangular, paired tooth-like process, tooth medial subbasal margin with small medial tooth (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6AFF96FE6FF839EE5FF816" box="[436,534,1964,1989]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 11b</figureCitation>
). Pygofer with wide anterior apodeme; pygofer lobe with elongate ventroapical sclerotized process; about 14 macrosetae dorsomedially (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A6AFF96FCF5F85AEF98F83B" box="[814,977,1999,2024]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 11a, 11b</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate length to width ratio 1.22–1.37 (n=5); laterobasal margin concave; apex broadly rounded; macrosetae in 2–3 irregular rows near apex (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FF44FF29ED4AFF07" box="[159,259,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11c</figureCitation>
). Valve transversely triangular, without anterior apodeme (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FC67FF29E869FF07" box="[956,1056,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11c</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with shaft elongate, sclerotized, straight in dorsal view, slightly curved in lateral view, apex with paired, acutely triangular tooth, directed ventrad, adpressed to shaft; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FD24FE91EFD5FECF" box="[767,924,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Figs 11d, 11e</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal paraphysis gracile, tubular, rightangled at base, apex acute, extending beyond apex of shaft (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FCADFEB2EF94FE93" box="[886,989,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11d</figureCitation>
). Style apophysis curvate, acuminate, elongated, curved dorsolaterally; preapical angle right-angled (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FCB3FED9EF81FEB6" box="[872,968,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11f</figureCitation>
); positioned medially in subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FF44FEFAECB7FE5B" box="[159,254,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11c</figureCitation>
). Connective with arms and stem of similar length (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FC98FEFAEFEAFE5B" box="[835,931,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A69FF95FCACFEE5EFEAFE5B" box="[887,931,368,392]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.1" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="g" value="11.0">11g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A69FF95FF1CFE01EFD9FE26" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
