<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A69FF95FF1CFCD1ED63FA86" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A69FF95FF1CFCD1ED63FA86" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FF1CFCD1ED7DFC8E" bold="true" box="[199,308,836,861]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FE98FCD1EE3BFC8E" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[323,626,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thigmacaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FE98FCD1EE3BFC8E" box="[323,626,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Discolopeus thigmacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has distinct features such as the adpressed apical teeth on the aedeagal shaft, right-angled aedeagal paraphysis, T-shaped dorsal apodeme, large acuminate, ventral pygofer lobe and bidentate spine on the ventral apex of abdominal tergite X. The subgenital plate has the basal lateral margin concave, in contrast to the straight margin of all other known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FC1AFC3AE802FC1B" authority="Stiller, 2019" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[961,1099,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FC1AFC3AE802FC1B" box="[961,1099,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Discolopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Colour patterns and shape of the crown resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FE01FC40EE08FC3F" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[474,577,981,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FE01FC40EE08FC3F" box="[474,577,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FD94FC40EEF7FC3F" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[591,702,981,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="copeus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FD94FC40EEF7FC3F" box="[591,702,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. copeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FD2EFC40EFEEFC3E" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[757,935,980,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FD2EFC40EFEEFC3E" box="[757,935,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Genitalia between these three species differ distinctly. The pygofer lobe in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FE2FFC6CEE14FBC3" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[500,605,1017,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FE2FFC6CEE14FBC3" box="[500,605,1017,1040]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two parts, a membranous ventral lobe and a sclerotized, compressed, dorsal lobe, curvate laterally and minutely toothed ventrally. The aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FB83FB88E881FBE7" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1112,1224,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FB83FB88E881FBE7" box="[1112,1224,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an enlarged, compressed shaft with paired ventral teeth. The pygofer lobe in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FCBCFBD4EF91FB8B" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[871,984,1089,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="copeus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FCBCFBD4EF91FB8B" box="[871,984,1089,1112]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. copeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is simple, with a short ventral and short medial sclerotized blunt tooth. The aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FD12FBF0EF74FBAF" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[713,829,1125,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="copeus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FD12FBF0EF74FBAF" box="[713,829,1125,1148]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. copeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the apex chisel-shaped. The pygofer lobe in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FA5AFBF0ED6FFB73" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FA5AFBF0ED6FFB73" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is lobulate and weakly sclerotized. 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FD6FFB12EFDAFB73" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[692,915,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="copeus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FD6FFB12EFDAFB73" box="[692,915,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Discolopeus copeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species with a depressed apophysis of the style. 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FEEFFB39EE58FB17" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[308,529,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FEEFFB39EE58FB17" box="[308,529,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Discolopeus arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the style apophysis compressed, as is the case in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FB75FB38E95CFB16" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1198,1301,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lissus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FB75FB38E95CFB16" box="[1198,1301,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D. lissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The point distribution map of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FEA8FB44EE79FB3B" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[371,560,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thigmacaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FEA8FB44EDCEFB3B" box="[371,391,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FE4FFB5AEE79FB3B" box="[404,560,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">thigmacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in 
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A69FF95FDB7FB5AEEA1FB3B" box="[620,744,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1466]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1474]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19a–c. Distribution maps of leafhopper species of Discolopeus gen.n. and associated plants. a. Hyaenanche globosa near Vanrhynsdorp and one record near Citrusdal (red squares); b. Potential natural distribution of D. copeus sp.n. in the southwestern parts of South Africa, Western Cape Province; c. Point distributions of D. colopeus sp.n., D. lissus sp.n., D. tetracaenus sp.n., D. thigmacaenus sp.n., D. triacaenus sp.n. and D. viraktamathi sp.n. in Western, Northern and Eastern Cape Provinces." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626849/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 19c. A</figureCitation>
number of species of leafhoppers in the genera 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FB27FB5AE818FADE" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FB27FB5AE9D1FB3B" box="[1276,1432,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Austroagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Austroagallia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FF4CFB61ECBEFADE" authorityName="Theron" authorityYear="1974" box="[151,247,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bloemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Bloemia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FEDEFB60EF3BFADF" authority=", Chlorita, Circulifer, Coloborrhis, Equeefa" authorityName="Chlorita, Circulifer, Coloborrhis, Equeefa" box="[261,882,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bonaspeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Bonaspeia, Chlorita, Circulifer, Coloborrhis, Equeefa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FC5BFB61EFACFADE" authorityName="Theron" authorityYear="1974" box="[896,997,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hadroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hadroca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FC2FFB61E818FADE" authorityName="Theron" authorityYear="1974" box="[1012,1105,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Johanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Johanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FB55FB61E954FADE" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1961" box="[1166,1309,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tzitzikamaia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FB55FB61E954FADE" box="[1166,1309,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Tzitzikamaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been collected on 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A69FF95FEFCFA82EDF0FAE3" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[295,441,1303,1328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Zygophyllaceae" genus="Zygophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A69FF95FEFCFA82EDF0FAE3" box="[295,441,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Zygophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
